          "slidetitle": "The Dependency Trap Explained",
          "subtitle": "When shortcuts replace genuine understanding",
          "slidecontent": "• Students using AI to complete tasks without engaging in the thinking process behind them\n• Repeated shortcuts that quietly erode problem-solving and critical reasoning skills\n• The brain learns by struggling\n• Dependency forms gradually, often before students (or teachers) notice anything is wrong\n• Confidence built on AI output rather than genuine personal understanding\n• A student who always borrows answers never discovers what they actually know",
