        {
          "number": 4,
          "slidetitle": "The Dependency Trap Explained",
          "subtitle": "When shortcuts replace genuine understanding",
          "slidecontent": "• AI does the thinking instead\n• Skills never fully develop\n• Confidence drops over time\n• Help becomes a requirement\n• Learning stalls without AI",
          "do_not_include": true
        },
        {
          "number": 5,
          "slidetitle": "The Dependency Trap Explained",
          "subtitle": "When shortcuts replace genuine understanding",
          "slidecontent": "• Students using AI to generate answers without engaging with the underlying concepts\n• Repeated shortcuts weaken the mental effort needed to build lasting knowledge\n• Skills fade fast\n• Over-reliance mirrors other dependency patterns, such as always using a calculator before understanding arithmetic\n• The problem is not the tool itself, but the habit of bypassing the thinking process entirely",
          "do_not_include": true
        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "slidetitle": "The Dependency Trap Explained",
          "subtitle": "When shortcuts replace genuine understanding",
          "slidecontent": "• Students using AI to complete tasks without first attempting them independently\n• Repeated reliance on AI answers gradually weakens problem-solving muscles\n• Skills fade fast\n• The brain strengthens through struggle, not through receiving ready-made solutions\n• Over time, students lose confidence in their own ability to think without assistance",
          "do_not_include": true
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "slidetitle": "Reclaiming Skills From AI",
          "subtitle": "Rebuilding Confidence Through Independent Practice",
          "slidecontent": "• Try tasks without AI first\n• Make mistakes on purpose\n• Check your own work\n• Build habits, not shortcuts\n• Celebrate small wins daily",
